id: pm-7dcf
title: "S3: move the --allow-audit-* override flag family out of core command registrations into pm-governance-audit (enforcement stays core)"
description: "Remove core registration of the six override flags: --allow-audit-update + --allow-audit-dep-update (pm update / update-many; registration-helpers.ts:527-532, update-many.ts:59-60), --allow-audit-comment (comments.ts:41), --allow-audit-note, --allow-audit-learning (learnings.ts:33-35), --allow-audit-release (register-operations.ts:573). The package re-registers them via registerFlags(targetCommand) per D1 on pm-fg0b; core keeps the ENFORCEMENT (audit-protection guard) and keeps reading the option VALUES generically (anyOptionTrue alias lists + allowAuditBypass merge in register-mutation.ts:1376/1671/1714) so plugin-supplied flags pass through unchanged. Bare-core fallback behavior (D2): non-owner audit-gated mutations without the plugin per the decision (--force only vs hard block). Update error-guidance.ts:703 ownership-conflict guidance to be capability-aware (only mention audit flags when the plugin is installed — pm-qljv/pm-ulqu class, render from declared contract domain per the pm-mpbb ledger). Test risk: pm-qfdd commander-singleton leak affects in-process dynamic-flag tests — use worker-bridge suites (pm-kvd0 pattern). Blocked by the D1/D2 decision."
